  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reinforcing Community Media Sustainability and the role of the media in the fight against Terrorism in the Sahel</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to reinforce community media sustainability and the role of the media in the fight against terrorism in the Sahel, this activity will 1) Ensure regional celebrations of World Radio Day and Women Make the News 2) Backstop policy development in the Gambia based on the Community Media Sustainability Policy series, and 3) In the framework of the United Nations Integrated Strategy for the Sahel, and as follow up to ongoing cooperation with UNOWAS and the Swiss Government, among others, ensure a regional conference at the level of the G5 Sahel and CEDEAO based on UNESCO resources including Terrorism and the Media: A Handbook for Journalists and the forthcoming Online Terrorism Resource Hub and Guidelines for Disaster Reporting.</narrative>
  </description>
